thread.title: Reich Earns USA South Rookie of the Week for Fifth Time in 2015
thread.title_full: Reich Earns USA South Rookie of the Week for Fifth Time in 2015

author: AccessWDUN Staff
title: Reich Earns USA South Rookie of the Week for Fifth Time in 2015
text:
By AccessWDUN Staff Related Articles UNG's Acimovic chosen as Peach Belt men's soccer Player of the Week Lady Lions crush Berea, 6-0 Piedmont men's soccer claims 2-0 win UNG women's soccer overpowers Motevallo, 4-1 
FAYETTEVILLE, N.C. — The USA South Athletic Conference has released the seventh Player of the Week listing for the fall with Cassidy Reich continuing her dominance in the league earning USA South Women's Soccer Rookie of the Week. Reich has now taken the honor five of the seven weeks the conference has awarded weekly honors. 
Reich scored three goals and had a helper over the week moving her total this season to 14 goals and 12 assists through 17 contests. The Lady Lions have a pair of contests remaining against Greensboro and Ferrum this upcoming weekend. 
The USA South Athletic Conference announces its weekly honor roll each Monday while the listing for golf is announced on Wednesdays. At least half of the teams in a sport must have competed within the previous week for honors to be awarded. Associated Tags : college soccer, Piedmont women's soccer © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
